{"recommendationid": "74373711", "author": {"steamid": "76561198043655647", "num_games_owned": 10737, "num_reviews": 246, "playtime_forever": 721, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 721, "last_played": 1597524471}, "language": "english", "review": "Mafia III is not the worst AAA to release but it is pretty bad. It's a shame because the first two hours are some of the best gaming has to offer. It's a great example of how the introduction/tutorial phase should be done, instead of bombarding you with text or teaching you the controls in the most boring way possible. The soundtrack, setting and characters are also very well done. Unfortunately that's where the good stops at, after the first two hours the "real" game play starts, and it's more or less the same thing over and over again until the end. 

At release the game was plagued by performance issues which have for the most part been fixed. Mirror reflections however are still worse than most games from the early 2000s. I only really ran into 1 bug: raising or lowering the volume (via the audio controls on my K70 LUX keyboard) caused the game to drop to 30 fps for a couple of seconds.

