{"recommendationid": "73470362", "author": {"steamid": "76561198011046975", "num_games_owned": 348, "num_reviews": 9, "playtime_forever": 1454, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0, "playtime_at_review": 1378, "last_played": 1747261399}, "language": "english", "review": "Reading through some of the other reviews for this title, I suppose your mileage may vary in terms of what the Definitive Edition update did. On my end, it seems to have slightly bumped the performance without having to do any workaround, whereas before this update, I had to do some tweaking on my end to get the game running just a bit worse than it does with this update. That said, on to the game itself.

I enjoy Mafia III's world, characters, gunplay, exploration, and one of my favorite aspects is how well I feel Clay feels to control. That said, and as many other reviews have stated, there isn't enough of that to help keep the player enagaged. Mafia III could have benefited from dynamic events happening around the city as you move from one mission to the next - that's really where the game dwindles. When moving around the city to start the next mission, be it side-story or main, there doesn't feel like there is much to do, aside from searching for a collectible here or there that may pop-up. The game, as a whole, also could have been optimized much better, too, but, that this point, it pretty much is what it is.

I think Mafia III is a fun time with an interesting batch of characters and story set within a detailed yet somewhat empty feeling world. If you like open world games, chances are you will enjoy this too.", "timestamp_created": 1596036312, "timestamp_updated": 1596036312, "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "weighted_vote_score": 0.5, "comment_count": 0, "steam_purchase": false, "received_for_free": false, "written_during_early_access": false, "primarily_steam_deck": false}

